obo:UBERON_0002421  a  owl:Class .

gomodel:SYNGO_4554  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 1: TREK-1 KO depolarizes membrane potential and increases input resistance of hippocampal pyramidal neurons.\nFigure 2: TREK-1 KO increases the excitability of CA1 pyramidal neurons.\nFigure 3: TREK-1 null alters dendritic sprouting and the number of spines\nFigure 4: TREK-1 KO increases excitatory and inhibitory synaptic transmission in CA1 pyramidal neurons.\nFigure 5: TREK-1 KO increases Functional Expression of Postsynaptic AMPA Receptors.\n\nDnyanada 11/06/2021: The enhanced functional expression of postsynaptic AMPA receptors is inferred from AMPA-EPSC electrophysiological measurements. This paper does not further investigate this phenotype (eg via immunocytochemistry of surface AMPAR) and hence the general term \"postsynaptic process...\" was used.. Experimental description: TREK-1 gene (Kcnk2) knockout (TREK-1 KO) mice were generated on a mixed background of C57BL6J and SV129 strains. Prior to this study, this TREK-1 KO line has been backcrossed with C57BL6J for more than ten generations in our laboratory." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-2916-7616" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" ;
        dc:date           "2022-04-29" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_4554" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

